Topic: CD010438 

Title: Thromboelastography (TEG) and rotational thromboelastometry (ROTEM) for trauma-induced coagulopathy in adult trauma patients with bleeding 

Objective:The objective was to determine the diagnostic accuracy of thromboelastography and rotational thromboelastometry for TIC in adult trauma patients with bleeding, using a reference standard of Prothrombin Time ratio and/or the International Normalized Ratio.